article.headline: Tennessee Tech 100, Tenn.-Martin 95
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Amadi McKenzie and Anthony Fisher each had 21 points to lead Tennessee Tech to a 100-95 win over Tennessee-Martin on Thursday night. Frank Davis added 20 points for the Golden Eagles (7-7, 10-14 Ohio Valley Conference), who were 10 of 17 from behind the 3-point arc. Marquis Weddle led the Skyhawks (7-7, 11-13) with 30 points, and Lester Hudson added 27 points, eight assists and 7 rebounds. Benzor Simmons had 18 points for Tennessee-Martin. Tennessee Tech went ahead 51-36 at the half, shooting 60 percent for the game from the floor. Tennessee-Martin never led, but nearly staged a comeback by shooting 58 percent after intermission.
